    {
      "levelGroup": "advanced",
      "title": "Mastering Urban Navigation",
      "cefrLevel": "B2",
      "summaryJa": "都市部での移動を円滑にするため、詳細なランドマークを用いたルート確認や道案内の受け方を学びます。",
      "sourceUrls": [
        "https://shoya9696.github.io/daily-shadowing-content/topics/evergreen/travel_culture/asking-for-directions"
      ],
      "sentences": [
        {
          "index": 0,
          "text": "Navigating an unfamiliar city often requires asking locals for precise directions and helpful tips.",
          "translationJa": "不慣れな街を移動するには、地元の人に正確な道順や役立つヒントを尋ねることが必要です。",
          "id": "advanced-2026-07-04-s01",
          "startMs": 0,
          "endMs": 5800,
          "sentenceAudioUrl": "https://shoya9696.github.io/daily-shadowing-content/audio/2026-07-04/advanced-s01.m4a"
        },
        {
          "index": 1,
          "text": "When you are unsure of your location, look for prominent landmarks like statues or towers.",
          "translationJa": "現在地が不明なときは、像や塔のような目立つランドマークを探してください。",
          "id": "advanced-2026-07-04-s02",
          "startMs": 6200,
          "endMs": 11333,
          "sentenceAudioUrl": "https://shoya9696.github.io/daily-shadowing-content/audio/2026-07-04/advanced-s02.m4a"
        },
        {
          "index": 2,
          "text": "Approach someone politely to inquire about the most efficient route to your intended destination.",
          "translationJa": "目的地への最も効率的なルートを尋ねるために、誰かに丁寧に声をかけましょう。",
          "id": "advanced-2026-07-04-s03",
          "startMs": 11733,
          "endMs": 16676,
          "sentenceAudioUrl": "https://shoya9696.github.io/daily-shadowing-content/audio/2026-07-04/advanced-s03.m4a"
        },
        {
          "index": 3,
          "text": "It is helpful to clarify whether the path involves steep hills or many stairs.",
          "translationJa": "その道に急な坂道や多くの階段があるかどうかを確認しておくと役立ちます。",
          "id": "advanced-2026-07-04-s04",
          "startMs": 17076,
          "endMs": 21253,
          "sentenceAudioUrl": "https://shoya9696.github.io/daily-shadowing-content/audio/2026-07-04/advanced-s04.m4a"
        },
        {
          "index": 4,
          "text": "Always confirm the estimated travel time to ensure you stay on your planned schedule.",
          "translationJa": "予定通りに行動できるよう、移動にかかる推定時間を常に確認しましょう。",
          "id": "advanced-2026-07-04-s05",
          "startMs": 21653,
          "endMs": 26125,
          "sentenceAudioUrl": "https://shoya9696.github.io/daily-shadowing-content/audio/2026-07-04/advanced-s05.m4a"
        },
        {
          "index": 5,
          "text": "Sometimes taking public transit is faster than walking through the busy city center streets.",
          "translationJa": "混雑した市内中心部を歩くよりも、公共交通機関を利用する方が早い場合もあります。",
          "id": "advanced-2026-07-04-s06",
          "startMs": 26525,
          "endMs": 31543,
          "sentenceAudioUrl": "https://shoya9696.github.io/daily-shadowing-content/audio/2026-07-04/advanced-s06.m4a"
        },
        {
          "index": 6,
          "text": "If you are still confused, do not hesitate to ask a second person for confirmation.",
          "translationJa": "それでも混乱している場合は、遠慮せずに別の人にもう一度確認してみてください。",
          "id": "advanced-2026-07-04-s07",
          "startMs": 31943,
          "endMs": 37072,
          "sentenceAudioUrl": "https://shoya9696.github.io/daily-shadowing-content/audio/2026-07-04/advanced-s07.m4a"
        },
        {
          "index": 7,
          "text": "Visualizing the map while listening to directions helps you remember the path much better.",
          "translationJa": "道順を聞きながら地図を頭の中で描くと、ルートをずっと覚えやすくなります。",
          "id": "advanced-2026-07-04-s08",
          "startMs": 37472,
          "endMs": 41958,
          "sentenceAudioUrl": "https://shoya9696.github.io/daily-shadowing-content/audio/2026-07-04/advanced-s08.m4a"
        },
        {
          "index": 8,
          "text": "Showing gratitude after receiving help reflects your appreciation for the local resident's valuable time.",
          "translationJa": "助けを受けた後に感謝を示すことは、地元住民の貴重な時間に対する敬意を表します。",
          "id": "advanced-2026-07-04-s09",
          "startMs": 42358,
          "endMs": 48231,
          "sentenceAudioUrl": "https://shoya9696.github.io/daily-shadowing-content/audio/2026-07-04/advanced-s09.m4a"
        },
        {
          "index": 9,
          "text": "Confidence in asking questions will make your travel experiences much more rewarding and enjoyable.",
          "translationJa": "質問することへの自信は、あなたの旅行体験をより実り多く楽しいものにするでしょう。",
          "id": "advanced-2026-07-04-s10",
          "startMs": 48631,
          "endMs": 53983,
          "sentenceAudioUrl": "https://shoya9696.github.io/daily-shadowing-content/audio/2026-07-04/advanced-s10.m4a"
        },
        {
          "index": 10,
          "text": "Remember that getting lost occasionally leads to discovering hidden gems within the city streets.",
          "translationJa": "時々道に迷うことは、街中の隠れた名所を発見することにつながると覚えておいてください。",
          "id": "advanced-2026-07-04-s11",
          "startMs": 54383,
          "endMs": 59266,
          "sentenceAudioUrl": "https://shoya9696.github.io/daily-shadowing-content/audio/2026-07-04/advanced-s11.m4a"
        }
      ],
